text: Desmiphora intonsa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Ernst Friedrich Germar in 1824. It is known from Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay, and Uruguay.BioLib.cz - Desmiphora intonsa. Retrieved 8 September 2014. ==References== Category:Desmiphora Category:Beetles described in 1824
